When you use Stack widget, every widget in the children of Stack widget will display like a layer. So instead of using Expended or Flexible as a child of Stack, use Container widget then add Expanded or Flexible as children.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    Stack(
        children: &lt;Widget&gt;[
          Container(
            width: double.infinity,
            height: double.infinity,
            child: Row(
              children: &lt;Widget&gt;[
                Expanded(
                  flex: 1,
                ),
                Expanded(
                  flex: 2,
                )
              ],
            ),
          )
        ],
      ),

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

By the way, if you want to add an icon at a corner or every where on the screen, use Positioned widget instead.

